\lambda = \left(\sum_{x_i} \frac{P(Y = x_i)}{x_i}\right)^{-1}.
P(Y = k) = (1-p)^{k-1}p
k = 1, 2, \ldots
\lambda = \frac{-q}{p \ln p}
P(X = k) = \lambda \frac{P(Y = k)}{k} = \lambda \frac{q^{k-1} p}{k} = \frac{\lambda p}{q} \frac{q^k}{k}.
